<br>
A rooted mob will exhibit undead-type aggro, i.e. it will attack the closest target on its hatelist regardless of taunt. <p><IMG SRC="http://lordfate.homestead.com/files/misc/sig.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ustrykerepeatedly.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stryke Repeatedly</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Antisocial Technophobe</span><br>  Posts: 634<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/27/01 9:48:02 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.evenstar.ca/wtf/wtfsmall.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: agro managment....</span><hr size=1> Yeah, that's what we wound up having to do, Korwin.  I'd recommend that in any situation regardless, since you can pick and choose who is taking the beats.  Just make sure the druid ain't rooting if those punks are mezzed, because that damage component kinda wakes 'em up. <p><hr align="center" size="1" COLOR="#006600">
